AGI - It could be held next Monday, April 1, in Washington, high-level talks between U.S. and Israeli officials on possible military operations in Rafah. The Cnn, citing US officials, reports that the date was not confirmed.
&nbsp;
Israeli prime minister Benjamin Netanyahu interrupted the interlocutions this week, after the US refused to vote on a UN resolution on the ceasefire in Gaza and the release of hostages still in the hands of Hamas.
&nbsp;
According to officials at the Cnn, the Israeli delegation proposed reprogramming the talks for Monday.
<h2>Truppe from Arab countries to be deployed in Gaza
The hypothesis of a multinational military force with troops from Arab countries to deploy in Gaza to secure order and escort the convoys of humanitarian aid was presented this week by Israeli Defense Minister Yoav Gallant on the occasion of his visit to Washington. Two senior Israeli officials report it, according to the American news site Axios.
&nbsp;
Sources believe that a multinational force could support an alternative to Hamas in the territory. " Such a move will build a governing body in the enclave that is not Hamas and address the growing problem of Israel with the United States regarding the humanitarian situation in Gaza," said a high Israeli official, according to Axios. Gallant would have asked the U.S. political and material support to his proposal during meetings with the Secretary of Defense, Lloyd Austin, Secretary of State Tony Blinken and National Security Counselor Jake Sullivan.
&nbsp;
The permanence of the Arab force would be limited to a transitional period. "There are progress in promoting this initiative both in terms of the Biden administration's will to discuss it, and in terms of the opening of the Arab countries to the idea," said an Israeli official.<br> According to an American official, quoted by Axios, one of the countries most interested in the initiative and Egypt, but the sending of Arab forces to Gaza would be subordinated to an official invitation of the Palestinian Authority.
